PRESS DIGEST - Vietnam - Oct 28 . These are some of the leading stories in the official Vietnamese press on Monday . Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy . - - - - VIETNAM NEWS - - Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet has instructed government ministries to take steps to help flood victims in southern Vietnam . - - Latest monthly inflation figures show a rise of 0 . 1 percent from September , bringing cumulative inflation over the past 10 months to 2 . 6 percent . - - - - NHAN DAN - - Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet has announced measures aimed at increasing budget revenue , which had reached only 62 . 3 percent of the 1996 target by the end of September . - - - - HANOI MOI - - A three - month course on State management for provincial officials ended last week . - - - - SAIGON GIAI PHONG - - The Ministry for Planning and Investment has withdrawn an investment licence for a big hotel and business complex joint - venture in the heart of Ho Chi Minh City . The report said the Swiss partner in the venture , Noga Saigon , had failed to meet its financial commitments . - - - - 
